The freshman Democratic posted Tweets in Sunday which implied that members of Congress support Israel
Politico Magazine contributing editor Joshua Zeitz tweeted:
"I'm one of those American Jews who oppose the occupation [of the West Bank and Gaza Strip], laments Israel's anti-democratic drift, and doesn't regard the country as especially central to my Jewish identity. And I knew exactly what the congresswoman meant. She might as well call us hook-nosed."
Omar is well known for her support for a movement known as BDS, for “boycott, divestment and sanctions” which criticizes Israel.
But it is not the first time she accused of anti-Semitism.
Omar says her rejection of the Israeli government refers towards its treatment fo the Palestinians
Omar has expressed regret for tweeting in 2012:
“Israel has hypnotized the world, may Allah awaken the people and help them see the evil doings of Israel.” 
Democratic House Speaker Nancy Pelosi  was accused of supporting the anti-Jewish campaign by Omar before she condemned the comments.
